The Second Annual Owen Temple Frio Fandango will be held Friday August 8th and Saturday August 9th near Concan, Texas in beautiful northern Uvalde County (about 80 miles west of San Antonio on Highway 90). The weekend will be a gathering of like minded folks enjoying music and good times on the Frio River in the Texas Hill Country.http://www.myspace.com/owentemplefriofandangohttp://tickets.frontgatetickets.com/choose.php?a=1&lid=22825&eid=27859Friday night will be an exclusive (open only to Fandango wristband holders) acoustic concert outdoors by Owen Temple, Adam Carroll and Jason Eady at a cabin by the Frio River.Additionally on Saturday night, August 9th, 2008, the Frio Fandango will host an open-to-the-public full Owen Temple Band show, with special guest Modern Day Drifters at House Pasture Cattle Company on River Road in Concan, Texas.

Venue: Ramblin Revival Song Workshop @ Inn of the Hills
Description: On Labor Day Weekend, Owen, Adam and Jason will share perspectives on songwriting with workshop participants in the Texas Hill Country. The workshop will be limited to 20 folks who are interested in learning more about the craft of songwriting and how these songwriters go about putting together songs.Over a series of one-on-one meetings and small group sessions, folks who come to the workshop can hear each songwriter give a process-oriented perspective on creating songs. The objective will be to trade notes with workshop attendees to help them put together songs that meet their creative goals.Spots for the workshop will be limited to 20, and spots will be made available, first come first served.A registration fee of $400 includes two nights lodging at the Inn of the Hills (check-in on Friday August 29, stay Saturday August 30, check-out on Sunday, August 31), access to two days of workshop sessions, and all song workshop materials.Click link below to find out more about this year’s workshop.   http://www.ramblinrevival.com

Kent Finlay Birthday ConcertKENT FINLAY BIRTHDAY CONCERTOn Monday  (Feb 7), at Cheatham Street Warehouse, Kent Finlay will be celebrating his 29th Birthday (again) with a concert / fundraiser to benefit the non-profit Cheatham Street Music Foundation.  More than thirty of Kent's favorite singer/songwriters will be coming together to donate their talents and help raise money for this worthy cause.  The list includes such notables as ADAM CARROLL, AL BARLOW, JOHN ARTHUR MARTINEZ, SHELLEY KING, RAY WYLIE HUBBARD, OWEN TEMPLE, MIKE ETHAN MESSICK, BILL WHITBECK, JAVI GARCIA, JORDAN MINOR, and many more . . . plus a generous sprinkling of unannounced surprise guests.  It is rumored that Gary Floater is possibly going to make one of his rare appearances at the event.WHEN:  Monday - Feb 7               Starts at 5:00 & goes till well past midnightBENEFITS:  Cheatham Street Music Foundation 501(c)(3)DONATION:  Minimum donation of $10.  (No donation too large)

100.1 KDRP presents to you the first ever Pick n' Chug at The Stripe.  The Stripe is located at 3712 Robinson, Austin, Texas 78722. The Pick n' Chug will consist of day drinking, music listening and chicken eatin'. Festivities will begin at 1pm. Artists you can expect to perform are...  Ray Wylie Hubbard Sons of Fathers Evan Felker of The Turnpike Troubadours Wood & Wire Owen Temple Halleyanna Finlay Kym Warner of the Greencards Carson McHone The Lonesome Heroes and many more...  The great Kurt McMahan will be MC and chief of harmonica. We will be grilling chicken and drinking lots of beer. A five dollar donation will be collected at the door to fuel the party and help out your local KDRP station. Parking is available across the street in the large empty parking lot. Bring your friends, bring your dog, bring your dogs friends. You don't want to miss the Pick N' Chug!!!

Summer afternoons become a gateway to good times in Shiner Texas as the ever popular “Shiner Sundays” make their return. To the delight of Shiner citizens, passer- through travelers, and music listeners from the area, Bill Pekar and Howard Gloor share the music and memories they have made in their travels with songs and guest artists. The event has proven to be a success, and provides the famous little town with the best acoustic music you will hear on any given Sunday.

Mudbugs & Guitars is an annual fundraising event held over the Memorial Day weekend, bringing together musicians and music lovers from diverse backgrounds and from many different states. Proceeds from Mudbugs & Guitars will benefit Soldier Songs and Voices, the Fighting Blindness Foundation, and  provide college scholarships to deserving students.

Description: Songfarmer: A 3 day songwriting workshop hosted by Gordy Quist and Owen Temple Songfarmer: A Songwriting Workshop in Austin, TX On the weekend of May 30-June 1, Gordy Quist and Owen Temple will launch Songfarmer, a songwriting retreat on Lake Travis in the beautiful hill country around Austin, Texas. The creative retreat will be limited to 10-12 folks who are interested in exploring the craft/process/art of songwriting in a collaborative group setting. Through small group discussion, some one-on-one mentorship, and some co-writing sessions, Gordy and Owen will focus on training the mind to always be songfarming/treasure hunting, and hope to build a community of new friends that will stay in touch and continue collaborating. The hope is that this relaxing, yet intensive weekend at a beautiful lakeside, hill country getaway, will renew your inspiration and commitment to the cultivation of better songs. To register or learn more about the workshop, visit www.songfarmer.com

The guys gather each week at Doug’s place in downtown Manchaca, Texas to bring you an in-depth, unique and entertaining show that explores the stories behind the songs and songwriters we all know and love. This show takes a laid-back and conversational approach to storytelling, with the hosts throwing caution and radio scripts to the wind.

Songfarmer: A 3 day songwriting workshop hosted by Gordy Quist and Owen Temple Songfarmer: A Songwriting Workshop in Austin, TX On the weekend of December 5-December 7, Gordy Quist and Owen Temple will host Songfarmer, a songwriting retreat on Lake Travis in the beautiful hill country around Austin, Texas. The creative retreat will be limited to 10-12 folks who are interested in exploring the craft/process/art of songwriting in a collaborative group setting. Through small group discussion, some one-on-one mentorship, and some co-writing sessions, Gordy and Owen will focus on training the mind to always be songfarming/treasure hunting, and hope to build a community of new friends that will stay in touch and continue collaborating. The hope is that this relaxing, yet intensive weekend at a beautiful lakeside, hill country getaway, will renew your inspiration and commitment to the cultivation of better songs. To register or learn more about the workshop, visit www.songfarmer.com

Venue: Lydaco Songwriting Workshop @ Unity of Columbia
Description: Owen is also teaching a 3-hour songwriting workshop, Songfarmer, earlier on April 18, from 10 am - 1 pm.  The cost is $45, and includes continental breakfast. You don't have to be a songwriter to attend the workshop to learn Owen's approach to writing songs.  The registration form is attached. You can pre-pay the workshop fee via paypal at: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/songwriting-workshop-with-owen-temple-tickets-15184976674?ref=ebtn Once upon a time, men and women would feel an urge to express something in song. They would sit down with a guitar and a piece of paper, and few words might emerge from the lips or on the page. But then nothing else would happen. The idea just sat there and failed to grow into a song. Or even worse, maybe the page was blank to begin with, and it stayed blank. But then one day, they started Songfarming. Songfarmer is a process oriented approach to writing songs, and Songfarmer is a series of habits, principles, techniques, and, ideally, a community of folks working together. It’s about taking the long view on writing songs: to develop the ongoing routines of songwriting so that you get songs today, tomorrow, and on into the future. A farmer doesn’t walk outside one day and just expect crops to burst forth from the ground, without daily preparation and steady application of habits, and songwriters should similarly collect “seeds” for songs, review them, work them gently until they grow. The farmer and songwriter both have principles and practices that come in handy in the day to day work. And the songwriter and the farmer both need patience to encounter frustrations as they stubbornly persist in the habits of growing things. At this songwriting workshop, Owen Temple talk about the Songfarming principles and what he has seen work for growing more and better songs. Cost:  $45 For information and reservations, email lydacomusic@gmail.com

Illinois River Jam is an annual camping and music gathering on the banks of the Illinois River in Tahlequah, Ok.  Since 2007, Illinois River Jam has hosted talented local and national songwriters and musicians in a laid back and beautiful environment. This event takes place after the summer season so we have the river recreation area all to ourselves! Camping is free with the ticket or lodging is available at nearby resorts. We are proud to keep this a SMALL gathering with none of the annoyances that go along with a big music fest. Supremely talented musicians in a beautiful setting. Kids 12 and under are free. Tent camping is included with ticket price.  Tickets only available right here!!  Limited RV or electric sites can be reserved for an additional fee by contacting Peyton's Place.  Tickets are limited so buy now and your wristbands will be waiting for you at the gate!  See you in September!!

Outdoor show by riverfront cabin. Bring a lawn chair and whatever you'd like to drink, and music will start about 7:30pm.  The Frio River Song Festival is known for being relaxed and informal, and this year's Frio River Festival is going to be even more relaxed and low key. It's happening on Friday night at the Truelove cabin (same site as all the years before).  This year, it will be Owen Temple, Adam Carroll and Chris Carroll doing the Friday night show on the hill by the cabin.  You know the drill- at 7:30 the acoustic show will start on Friday, just as it gets breezy and the sun goes drops over the hill. Bring lawn chairs and drinks/snacks. You can get tickets in advance here and at the cabin on the night of the show- $20 per person for folks that want to join us.  Make your reservations at the Eventbrite link (https://www.eventbrite.com/e/frio-river-song-festival-tickets-35297168782), and we'll send the usual details/directions a week before the show. Just email mary@frioriversongfestival.com with any questions.  Wishing you many music-filled, starry nights til then!
